<p>
For those of you who don't know me I'm a Ph.D. student at 
North Carolina State University in the Computer Science Department.  
I currently have a Masters of Computer Science, a Bachelor of Science 
in Computer Science, and a Bachelor of Science in Computer Engineering.

<P> My main areas of interest are formal methods, operating systems, and
programming languages.  I'm working with
<!WA8><a href="http://www4.ncsu.edu/eos/users/r/rance/WWW/"> Dr. Rance Cleaveland</a>
as a research assistant.  </P>

<P> This summer my wife, Seunghee Lee, and I went on a vacation to
Europe.  If you'd like to see a few pictures from our trip 
click <!WA9><a href="http://www4.ncsu.edu/~bwmott/www/europe/europe.html">here</a>.
</p>

<hr>

<p>If you're interested in any of the stuff I've developed checkout the
following links:</p>

